(332, 'Blue Lotus Powder', 'Blue Lotus powder is a natural herbal supplement made from the dried petals of the Nymphaea caerulea flower. It is traditionally used for its calming, mood-enhancing, and mild sedative effects. Often mixed into teas, smoothies, or other beverages, it offers a holistic approach to relaxation and stress relief.', '<p>Blue Lotus powder is derived from the petals of the Nymphaea caerulea, also known as the blue Egyptian lotus. This plant has been revered since ancient times, particularly in Egyptian culture, where it was associated with spiritual and medicinal practices. The powder is made by drying and grinding the petals into a fine consistency, preserving the flower\'s natural compounds. Known for its mildly sweet, floral flavor, Blue Lotus powder is often used in teas, smoothies, and other beverages, offering a convenient way to incorporate its benefits into daily routines.</p><p>Traditionally, Blue Lotus powder is celebrated for its calming and mood-enhancing properties. It contains a variety of alkaloids, flavonoids, and other phytochemicals that contribute to its effects. When consumed, it is said to promote relaxation, reduce anxiety, and improve overall mood. Some users also report mild sedative effects, making it a popular choice for those looking to unwind or improve sleep quality. Additionally, the powder is believed to have aphrodisiac qualities, enhancing intimacy and connection.</p><p>Beyond its calming effects, Blue Lotus powder is appreciated for its holistic approach to wellness. It is often used in aromatherapy and holistic medicine to support emotional and mental well-being. The versatile nature of the powder allows it to be easily added to various foods and drinks, making it a flexible supplement for those seeking natural remedies. As with any herbal supplement, it is important to use Blue Lotus powder responsibly and consult with a healthcare professional, especially if combining it with other medications or treatments.</p>', 'simple', '1 item', 500, 35, 22.00, 20.24, 8.00, 0, NULL, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MAR05', 0, 'in_stock', 'Blue Lotus Powder', 'Blue Lotus powder, derived from the petals of the Nymphaea caerulea flower, holds a rich history of cultural significance and medicinal use dating back to ancient civilizations. Revered in Egyptian culture as a symbol of spirituality and regeneration, Blue Lotus has long been associated with relaxation, tranquility, and heightened states of consciousness. The powder is meticulously crafted by drying and grinding the petals, preserving its natural compounds and aromatic properties.\n\nThe therapeutic potential of Blue Lotus powder lies in its diverse array of phytochemicals, including alkaloids, flavonoids, and terpenoids. These compounds work synergistically to offer a range of benefits, from promoting relaxation and reducing stress to enhancing mood and inducing mild euphoria. Many users report feelings of calmness and mental clarity after consuming Blue Lotus powder, making it a popular choice for meditation, yoga, or simply unwinding after a long day.\n\nIn addition to its calming effects, Blue Lotus powder is often prized for its aphrodisiac qualities. Historically, it has been used to enhance libido, heighten sensory experiences, and foster intimacy. Some users incorporate Blue Lotus powder into romantic rituals or sensual experiences, believing it to stimulate desire and deepen connections with partners. Its subtle yet profound effects on mood and arousal make it a versatile supplement for individuals seeking to enrich their emotional and physical well-being.\n\nBlue Lotus powder offers a holistic approach to wellness, seamlessly integrating into various lifestyles and wellness practices. Whether brewed into a tea, blended into a smoothie, or added to baked goods, its mild, floral flavor enhances the sensory experience while delivering its therapeutic benefits. However, it\'s essential to approach Blue Lotus powder with mindfulness and respect for its potency. As with any herbal supplement, moderation is key, and individuals should consult with a healthcare professional before incorporating it into their wellness routine, particularly if they have underlying health conditions or are taking medications.', 1901, 1901, NULL, 'Your order is likely to reach you within 6-9 days.', NULL, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'blue-lotus-powder', 1, 22, 1, 1, 'url', 'physical', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, 'center', 64, NULL, 'fixed', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-05-24 00:59:20', '2024-05-24 00:59:20'),
(333, 'Loose Leaf Tea', 'Loose leaf tea consists of whole or partially broken tea leaves, offering a higher quality and fresher taste compared to tea bags. It allows for customizable brewing, with options to adjust flavor intensity and strength. Loose leaf tea is appreciated by tea enthusiasts for its rich aroma, nuanced flavors, and potential health benefits.', '<p>Loose leaf tea represents the purest form of tea, offering a superior quality and flavor profile compared to tea bags. Comprising whole or partially broken tea leaves, loose leaf tea allows for a more nuanced and complex infusion, as the leaves have more room to expand and release their essential oils and flavors. This results in a richer and more aromatic cup of tea, with a depth of flavor that cannot be achieved with pre-packaged tea bags.</p><p>The process of brewing loose leaf tea involves using a tea infuser or strainer to steep the leaves directly in hot water. This method allows for optimal extraction of the tea\'s essential components, including polyphenols, antioxidants, and caffeine, resulting in a flavorful and aromatic beverage. Additionally, brewing loose leaf tea provides the opportunity for customization, as users can adjust the quantity of tea leaves, water temperature, and steeping time to suit their preferences and desired strength of flavor.</p><p>In addition to its superior taste and aroma, loose leaf tea offers environmental benefits compared to tea bags. By choosing loose leaf tea, consumers reduce waste associated with single-use tea bags and packaging materials. Furthermore, many loose leaf teas are sourced from sustainable and ethically managed tea gardens, supporting environmentally friendly practices and fair labor standards. Overall, loose leaf tea provides a premium tea-drinking experience that is both environmentally conscious and deeply satisfying for tea enthusiasts.</p>', 'simple', '1 item', 500, 50, 28.00, 25.20, 10.00, 0, NULL, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MAR06', 0, 'in_stock', 'Loose Leaf Tea', 'Loose leaf tea is the epitome of tea purity, offering an unparalleled sensory experience and depth of flavor compared to its bagged counterparts. Comprised of whole or partially broken tea leaves, loose leaf tea preserves the natural oils and delicate nuances of the tea plant, resulting in a brew that is both complex and satisfying. The larger surface area of loose leaf tea allows for optimal infusion during brewing, ensuring that every cup is imbued with the full spectrum of flavors and aromas inherent in the tea leaves.\n\nBrewing loose leaf tea is a ritualistic process that involves attention to detail and a reverence for the art of tea making. Tea enthusiasts typically use specialized equipment such as tea infusers, teapots, or gaiwans to steep the leaves properly. By controlling factors such as water temperature, steeping time, and leaf-to-water ratio, aficionados can tailor each cup of loose leaf tea to their exact specifications, resulting in a personalized and exquisite tea-drinking experience.\n\nBeyond its superior taste and aroma, loose leaf tea offers numerous health benefits attributed to its rich concentration of antioxidants, polyphenols, and other bioactive compounds. These substances have been linked to various health-promoting effects, including improved heart health, enhanced immune function, and reduced risk of chronic diseases. By incorporating loose leaf tea into their daily routine, individuals can harness the nutritional and wellness benefits of tea while indulging in its sensory pleasures.\n\nMoreover, choosing loose leaf tea is a conscious decision that aligns with sustainable and eco-friendly practices. Unlike tea bags, which often contain plastic and other non-biodegradable materials, loose leaf tea generates minimal waste and can be composted after use. Additionally, many loose leaf teas are sourced from ethically managed tea gardens that prioritize environmental sustainability and fair labor practices, ensuring that every cup of tea supports both personal well-being and planetary health.', 1906, 1906, NULL, 'Your order is likely to reach you within 3-5 days.', NULL, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'loose-leaf-tea', 1, 22, 1, 1, 'url', 'physical', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, 'center', 66, NULL, 'fixed', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-05-24 01:06:33', '2024-05-24 01:06:33'),
