(339, 'Psyllium husk', 'Psyllium husk is a natural dietary fiber derived from the seeds of the Plantago ovata plant. It\'s commonly used as a gentle laxative to relieve constipation and promote regular bowel movements. Additionally, psyllium husk can help manage cholesterol levels and support digestive health.', '<p>Psyllium husk is a soluble fiber derived from the seeds of the Plantago ovata plant, native to parts of Asia, the Mediterranean region, and North Africa. It\'s often utilized as a natural remedy to alleviate constipation and promote digestive health due to its ability to absorb water and form a gel-like substance in the intestines. This gel helps soften stool and adds bulk, making it easier to pass, thereby relieving constipation and supporting regular bowel movements.</p><p>In addition to its role in relieving constipation, psyllium husk has been shown to have other health benefits. One notable benefit is its potential to help lower cholesterol levels. The soluble fiber in psyllium husk binds to cholesterol in the digestive tract, preventing its absorption into the bloodstream. This can lead to reduced levels of LDL (bad) cholesterol, which is associated with a lower risk of heart disease. Regular consumption of psyllium husk, as part of a balanced diet, may therefore contribute to improved heart health.</p><p>Furthermore, psyllium husk can be incorporated into a variety of foods and beverages to increase their fiber content. It\'s commonly found in fiber supplements, breakfast cereals, and baked goods, as well as in powdered form for easy mixing into smoothies or yogurt. When consuming psyllium husk, it\'s important to drink plenty of water to prevent potential digestive issues and ensure its effectiveness in promoting regularity and supporting overall digestive wellness.</p>', 'simple', '1 item', 500, 50, 20.00, 19.60, 2.00, 0, NULL, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'MAR12', 0, 'in_stock', 'Psyllium husk', 'Psyllium husk, derived from the seeds of the Plantago ovata plant, is a versatile and natural dietary fiber renowned for its ability to promote digestive health and relieve constipation. As a soluble fiber, psyllium husk absorbs water in the digestive tract, forming a gel-like substance that helps soften stool and facilitate bowel movements. This gentle laxative effect makes it a popular choice for individuals seeking relief from occasional constipation or irregularity, offering a natural alternative to harsher chemical laxatives.\n\nBeyond its role in digestive health, psyllium husk is also known for its potential to support heart health by helping to lower cholesterol levels. The soluble fiber in psyllium husk binds to cholesterol in the intestines, preventing its absorption into the bloodstream. Regular consumption of psyllium husk as part of a healthy diet may contribute to reduced levels of LDL (bad) cholesterol, thus lowering the risk of heart disease and promoting cardiovascular wellness.\n\nOne of the notable qualities of psyllium husk is its versatility in culinary applications. It can be easily incorporated into a variety of foods and beverages to boost their fiber content without significantly altering taste or texture. Psyllium husk powder can be mixed into smoothies, yogurt, or oatmeal for a convenient way to increase daily fiber intake. It\'s also commonly found in fiber supplements, breakfast cereals, and baked goods, offering a convenient and accessible means of adding fiber to the diet.\n\nHowever, it\'s important to consume psyllium husk with an adequate amount of water to prevent potential digestive issues such as bloating or intestinal obstruction. Additionally, individuals with certain medical conditions, such as gastrointestinal disorders or allergies to psyllium, should consult with a healthcare professional before incorporating psyllium husk into their diet. Overall, psyllium husk offers a natural and effective way to support digestive health, improve regularity, and promote overall wellness when used as part of a balanced diet and healthy lifestyle.', 1936, 1936, NULL, 'Your order is likely to reach you within 3-5 days.', NULL, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'psyllium-husk', 1, 22, 1, 1, 'url', 'physical', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, 'center', 66, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-05-24 02:05:34', '2024-05-24 02:05:34'),
